{"title": "Temporary Substitute", "content": "So, you're shooting a weekly TV series, but one of your actors can't make it that week because of illness/rehab/a lengthy film shoot and the scripts are already written with a big role for their character? What do you do? Call in a Temporary Substitute, of course!\n\nSimilar, but not identical, to a Suspiciously Similar Substitute. This is where a script has clearly been hastily rewritten to give one character the plot that would have been given to the character who can't make it that week. That it may involve someone being Not Himself for the week is often unavoidable. A Suspiciously Similar Substitute is permanent, a Temporary Substitute is (hopefully) temporary; the lines blur, of course, when you're not sure if the original character is going to come back.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TemporarySubstitute", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HarryPotter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/OurMissBrooks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Frasier", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StargateSG1", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AmandaTapping", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StargateAtlantis", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekTheOriginalSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/GeorgeTakei", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheGreenBerets", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CSI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/WilliamPetersen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LucyLawless", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/XenaWarriorPrincess", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DirtySexyMoney", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Angel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AlexisDenisof", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AlysonHannigan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ElChavoDelOcho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JasonDavidFrank", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/PowerRangersDinoThunder", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/GetSmart", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Gorgo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MysteryScienceTheater3000", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TouchOfSatan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.